<subSubSection id="8765AE46E31C210EC442706F919D9004" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="B4F4073030213C4D090111FCEA15F59D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="519ABD5F77B780419659D1D3B07F4977" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Endemic to the Vallegrande area in the Bolivian inter-Andean valleys where it is uncommon in open grassy scrubland on hillsides from 1900 to 2200(-2500) m.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F616965EAAB8AC444378A74BADFBA14F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="26068C5B7A69951CB54BFBC819F1ACB4" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">BOLIVIA. Santa Cruz</emphasis>
: Vallegrande area, 
<emphasis id="8FC55A8B7899ACE859D39CDECDE7BCAF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. Vargas</emphasis>
33 (NY); road to Tierras Nuevas, 
<emphasis id="4D443DF7B9CF53ACF7299232337C52FE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. Nee et al.</emphasis>
37406 (NY); on descent to Piraimiri, 
<emphasis id="8B2754D5B5F3CC4CE048814DB68EA1D1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">J.R.I. Wood et al.</emphasis>
21743 (LPB); Vallegrande-Postrervalle, 
<emphasis id="7EE868DF792D7E4F58E48FF0EEFCB57A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
G.A. 
<taxonomicName id="E3E88CC9A344132B527B080A55F1D40C" class="Insecta" family="Tingidae" genus="Parada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Parada</taxonomicName>
et al.
</emphasis>
5326 (MO, USZ).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3FE35B30F40340B7D0D0839E0681198C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="EA6BDA9D5EDBC6BD66C5336A18A4AB45" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6F6987A8326EEB5091973F436BB7F353" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">This appears to be a rather isolated species morphologically. The subterminal inflorescence suggests it is essentially erect or ascending in habit, as indicated by most field notes, but it is unlike most erect species in South America in its broad leaves and Andean habitat.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
